EFSF Seen as Banks’ Backstop If Greece Defaults, FTD Says

-- B y   T o n y   C z u c z k a
-- 
2011-09-15T06:19:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/efsf-seen-as-banks-backstop-if-greece-defaults-ftd-says.html
Europe ’s rescue fund would have to
be used to bail out banks facing losses on Greek sovereign bonds
if the country defaults, the  Financial Times Deutschland
reported , citing people in  Germany ’s governing coalition it
didn’t identify.  The comments show that European policy makers are
considering the possibility of a Greek default, the newspaper
reported today. The fund is known as the European Financial
Stability Facility.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Tony Czuczka in Berlin at 
 aczuczka@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Hertling at  jhertling@bloomberg. 